sampled:
 Work, work, prepared for us
Field and forest bearing fruit,
Brooks flowing, sunbeams glowing,
Music of birds in sweet accord;
Earth, 'tis yours, and yours alone
To give to us, and deny not;
Complete, if granted, if denied,
Work, work, prepared for us.

Work, work, looking unto Him;
Trusting, beholding, nothing can
Detract from earnest, hopeful toil,
Labor untiring, patient, slow;
Nearer, dear Master, to thy side
If follow thou, or if thou lead;
Work, work, looking unto Him;
Forth to his service, glad and free,
With earnest prayer, and strong endeavor,
We cast our lots by thy dear cord,
Work, work, looking unto Him.

Work, work, beloved, beyond
This transitory world, prepared for us;
In the eternal city, where
The need of toil shall be o'er;
Where thorns no longer shall distress,
And where the water-brooks shall
Glide through the fair and fertile plains,
And happiness, from thy bright throne,
Shall flow, and nevermore cease;
Work, work, prepared for us.
